card.name: Super Conductor Tyranno
card.description: Once per turn: You can Tribute 1 monster; inflict 1000 damage to your opponent. This card cannot declare an attack the turn this effect is activated.

card.name: Kabazauls
card.description: A huge monster in the shape of a hippopotamus. The sneezing from his gigantic body is so fierce that people mistake it for a hurricane.

card.name: Sabersaurus
card.description: This normally gentle dinosaur enjoys relaxing in its nest in the prairies. If it becomes angered, it turns terribly ferocious.

card.name: Mad Sword Beast
card.description: If this card attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage.

card.name: Gilasaurus
card.description: You can Special Summon this card (from your hand). If Summoned this way: Activate this effect; your opponent can Special Summon 1 monster from their GY.

card.name: Dark Driceratops
card.description: If this card attacks a Defense Position monster, inflict piercing battle damage.

card.name: Hyper Hammerhead
card.description: At the end of the Damage Step, if an opponent's monster that battled this card is not destroyed: Return that opponent's monster to the hand.

card.name: Black Tyranno
card.description: If the only cards your opponent controls are Defense Position monsters, this card can attack directly.

card.name: Tyranno Infinity
card.description: The original ATK of this card is the number of your banished Dinosaur-Type monsters x 1000.

card.name: Hydrogeddon
card.description: When this card destroys an opponent's monster by battle and sends it to the GY: You can Special Summon 1 "Hydrogeddon" from your Deck.

card.name: Oxygeddon
card.description: If this card is destroyed by battle with a Pyro monster and sent to the GY: Each player takes 800 damage.

card.name: Black Ptera
card.description: When this card is sent from the field to the Graveyard, except by being destroyed by battle: Return it to the hand.

card.name: Black Stego
card.description: If this Attack Position card is targeted for an attack: Change this card to Defense Position.

card.name: Ultimate Tyranno
card.description: This card can attack all monsters your opponent controls, once each. During your Battle Phase, if you control an "Ultimate Tyranno" that can attack, monsters other than "Ultimate Tyranno" cannot attack.

card.name: Miracle Jurassic Egg
card.description: While face-up on the field, this card cannot be banished. Each time a Dinosaur-Type monster(s) is sent to your Graveyard, place 2 counters on this card. You can Tribute this card; Special Summon 1 Dinosaur-Type monster from your Deck whose Level is less than or equal to the number of counters that were on this card.

card.name: Babycerasaurus
card.description: If this card is destroyed by a card effect and sent to the Graveyard: Special Summon 1 Level 4 or lower Dinosaur-Type monster from your Deck.

card.name: Big Evolution Pill
card.description: After this card's activation, it remains on the field, but destroy it during your opponent's 3rd End Phase. Tribute 1 Dinosaur-Type monster to activate this card; while this card is face-up on the field, you can Normal Summon Level 5 or higher Dinosaur-Type monsters without Tributing.

card.name: Tail Swipe
card.description: Target 1 Level 5 or higher Dinosaur-Type monster you control; if that Dinosaur-Type monster is still face-up on the field, choose up to 2 monsters your opponent controls that have a lower Level than it, or are face-down, and return them to the hand.

card.name: Jurassic World
card.description: All Dinosaur-Type monsters gain 300 ATK and DEF.

card.name: Sebek's Blessing
card.description: If your monster inflicts battle damage to your opponent by a direct attack: Gain the same amount of LP.

card.name: Riryoku
card.description: Target 2 face-up monsters on the field; halve the ATK of 1 monster, and if you do, add that lost ATK to the other monster. These effects last until the end of this turn.

card.name: Mesmeric Control
card.description: During your opponent's next turn after you activate this card, your opponent cannot change the battle positions of monsters, except with a card effect.

card.name: Mystical Space Typhoon
card.description: Target 1 Spell/Trap on the field; destroy that target.

card.name: Megamorph
card.description: While your LP is lower than your opponent's, the equipped monster's ATK becomes double its original ATK. While your LP is higher, the equipped monster's ATK becomes half its original ATK.

card.name: Heavy Storm
card.description: Destroy all Spell and Trap Cards on the field.

card.name: Lightning Vortex
card.description: Discard 1 card; destroy all face-up monsters your opponent controls.

card.name: Magical Mallet
card.description: Shuffle any number of cards from your hand into the Deck, then draw that same number of cards.

card.name: Hunting Instinct
card.description: When a monster(s) is Special Summoned to your opponent's field (except during the Damage Step): Special Summon 1 Dinosaur monster from your hand.

card.name: Survival Instinct
card.description: Banish any number of Dinosaur-Type monsters from your Graveyard; gain 400 Life Points for each Dinosaur-Type monster banished to activate this card.

card.name: Volcanic Eruption
card.description: During your End Phase, if you control "Jurassic World": Destroy all cards on the field.

card.name: Seismic Shockwave
card.description: Destroy this card during your 3rd Standby Phase after activation. Activate this card when a face-up Dinosaur-Type monster you control is destroyed and sent to the Graveyard (except during the Damage Step): Choose 3 of your opponent's unused Spell & Trap Zones. Those Zones cannot be used. If this card destroys itself: You can target 1 Dinosaur-Type monster in your Graveyard; add that target to your hand.

card.name: Magical Arm Shield
card.description: When your opponent declares an attack while you control a monster: Target 1 face-up monster your opponent controls, except the attacking monster; take control of that target until the end of the Battle Phase, and if you do, it is attacked instead, and you proceed to damage calculation.

card.name: Negate Attack
card.description: When an opponent's monster declares an attack: Target the attacking monster; negate the attack, then end the Battle Phase.

card.name: Goblin Out of the Frying Pan
card.description: Pay 500 Life Points. Negate the activation of a Spell Card and return it to the owner's hand.

card.name: Malfunction
card.description: Pay 500 Life Points. Negate the activation of a Trap Card and return it to its original position.

card.name: Fossil Excavation
card.description: Activate this card by discarding 1 card, then target 1 Dinosaur-Type monster in your Graveyard; Special Summon that target. Negate the effects of that monster on the field. When this card leaves the field, destroy that monster. When that monster is destroyed, destroy this card.
